TY  - JOUR
AU  - Kotlikoff, Laurence J.
AU  - Gokhale, Jagadeesh
T1  - Estimating a Firm's Age-Productivity Profile Using the Present Value of Workers' Earnings*
PY  - 1992
Y1  - 1992/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/2118386
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 107
IS  - 4
SP  - 1215
EP  - 1242
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - In hiring new workers, risk-neutral employers equate the present expected value of a worker's compensation to the present expected value of his/her productivity. Data detailing how present expected compensation varies with the age of hire, therefore, embed information about how productivity varies with age. This paper infers age-productivity profiles using data on the present expected value of earnings of new hires of a Fortune 1000 firm. For each of the five occupation/sex groups considered, productivity falls with age, with productivity exceeding earnings when young and vice versa when old.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2118386
ER  - 



